kNames()` from hooks.go\n\n**Files:**\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/lifecycle.go` - inline the hook names list\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/hooks.go` - delete `GetHookNames()`\n\n### 4. Remove `removeEntireHooksFromMatchers()` pass-through\n\n`removeEntireHooksFromMatchers()` just calls `removeEntireHooks()`. The comment says \"Same logic\" — confirmed identical.\n\nReplace all 4 call sites with `removeEntireHooks()` and delete the function.\n\n**factoryaidroid/hooks.go:**\n- Lines 129-130: replace in `InstallHooks` force path\n- Lines 323-324: replace in `UninstallHooks`\n- Lines 525-530: delete function\n\n### 5. Simplify `addHookToMatcher()`\n\nThe `matcherName == \"\"` branch is identical to the general case because `matcher.Matcher == \"\"` equals `matcher.Matcher == matcherName` when matcherName is `\"\"`.\n\nSimplify from 32 lines to ~8 lines:\n\n```go\nfunc addHookToMatcher(matchers []FactoryHookMatcher, matcherName, command string) []FactoryHookMatcher {\n    entry := FactoryHookEntry{Type: \"command\", Command: command}\n    for i := range matchers {\n        if matchers[i].Matcher == matcherName {\n            matchers[i].Hooks = append(matchers[i].Hooks, entry)\n            return matchers\n        }\n    }\n    return append(matchers, FactoryHookMatcher{Matcher: matcherName, Hooks: []FactoryHookEntry{entry}})\n}\n```\n\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/hooks.go` lines 462-494\n\n## Files Modified (summary)\n\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/factoryaidroid.go`\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/factoryaidroid_test.go`\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/hooks.go`\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/lifecycle.go`\n- `cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/agent_test.go`\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\n```\n\nAll existing tests for `InstallHooks`, `UninstallHooks`, `AreHooksInstalled`, `ParseHookEvent`, and hook behavior should continue to pass unchanged. The 